article.headline: Troy 71, Louisiana-Monroe 70
article.story: MONROE, La. -- Brandon Hazzard scored 13 points and hit a key 3-pointer to lift Troy to a 71-70 win over Louisiana-Monroe on Saturday. The Trojans (9-10, 4-3 Sun Belt Conference), who trailed 40-36 at halftime, moved into the lead at 66-65 with 3:23 left on a Richard Delk basket. Louisiana-Monroe (5-13, 1-6) regained the advantage on a Malcolm Thomas jumper, then Delk missed the front end of a one-and-one. Hazzard hit his 3-pointer with 31 seconds left to give Troy a 69-67 lead and teammate Michael Vogler added two free throws with 16 seconds on the clock. After Louisiana-Monroe's Lawrence Gilbert hit a 3-pointer with 3 seconds remaining, the Warhawks ran out of time. Delk added 12 points and five rebounds for Troy. Thomas led Louisiana-Monroe with 20 points on 7-of-19 shooting. Gilbert had 17 points and 11 rebounds and Dynile Ford added 15 points.
